\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Temporal resolution of auditory neurons A1/A2. (A) Schematic of the thorax ganglion in acrtiid moth. (B) Schematic of the acrtiid moth ear, illustrating the electrophysiological recordings from the auditory neurons A1 and A2. (C) Spike raster plot (spike timing) from one recording session in response to a rectangular amplitude modulation with a pulse duration of 10~ms and a gap of 20~ms (period of 30~ms). (D) Mean vector strength over gap size from three different animals for a pulse duration of 10~ms. White symbols: non-significant values, black symbols: significant values. (E) Same as (D) but for a pulse duration of 5~ms. (F) Spike raster plot (spike timing) from one recording session in response to artificial moth pulse trains with a pulse duration of 2~ms and a gap of 20~ms. (G) Mean vector strength over gap size from three different animals for an artificial moth pulse duration of 2~ms. White symbols: non-significant values, black symbols: significant values. (H) Same as (G) but for a pulse duration of 0.5~ms. }}{12}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:02}{{2}{12}{Temporal resolution of auditory neurons A1/A2. (A) Schematic of the thorax ganglion in acrtiid moth. (B) Schematic of the acrtiid moth ear, illustrating the electrophysiological recordings from the auditory neurons A1 and A2. (C) Spike raster plot (spike timing) from one recording session in response to a rectangular amplitude modulation with a pulse duration of 10~ms and a gap of 20~ms (period of 30~ms). (D) Mean vector strength over gap size from three different animals for a pulse duration of 10~ms. White symbols: non-significant values, black symbols: significant values. (E) Same as (D) but for a pulse duration of 5~ms. (F) Spike raster plot (spike timing) from one recording session in response to artificial moth pulse trains with a pulse duration of 2~ms and a gap of 20~ms. (G) Mean vector strength over gap size from three different animals for an artificial moth pulse duration of 2~ms. White symbols: non-significant values, black symbols: significant values. (H) Same as (G) but for a pulse duration of 0.5~ms}{figure.2}{}}
